FAQs
What are the tuition fees for medical programs in Serbia?
Tuition fees for medical programs in Serbia range from €5,000 to €8,000 per year, depending on the university and program.

Are medical degrees from Serbia recognized internationally?
Yes, medical degrees from Serbian universities are recognized globally and meet European Union standards.

Do Serbian universities offer scholarships for international students?
Some universities in Serbia offer scholarships and financial aid to international students based on academic performance and financial need.

What is the duration of medical studies in Serbia?
The duration of medical studies in Serbia is typically six years, which includes pre-clinical and clinical training.

Can international students work while study in Serbia?
International students are allowed to work part-time during their studies in Serbia, but it is important to check the specific regulations and visa requirements.

